   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Tabular Prediction with SAP-RPT-1 and the Product Catalog\n",
    "\n",
    "In this demo, we will explore how to use **SAP-RPT-1** (Relational Prediction Transformer) to predict missing values in tabular data. Using the same product catalog from the RAG demo, we will ask RPT-1 to predict the **RATING** of products based on their attributes — without any model training or fine-tuning."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Learning Objectives\n",
    "By the end of this demo, you will be able to:\n",
    "- Understand what SAP-RPT-1 is and how it differs from LLMs.\n",
    "- Set up the SAP AI Core client and use the native `RPTClient` from the Generative AI Hub SDK.\n",
    "- Prepare tabular data in the RPT-1 prediction format using pydantic models.\n",
    "- Interpret RPT-1 predictions and confidence scores.\n",
    "- Apply RPT-1 to a real product catalog dataset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Requirements\n",
    "\n",
    "Before starting the Jupyter Notebook steps, ensure the following:\n",
    "- SAP AI Core instance (extended plan)\n",
    "- SAP-RPT-1 model available in your AI Core instance (no deployment needed — `RPTClient` resolves the model by name)\n",
    "- `env_config.json` with your AI Core credentials (same file used in the RAG notebook)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## What is SAP-RPT-1?\n",
    "\n",
    "**SAP-RPT-1** (Relational Prediction Transformer 1) is a **Relational Foundation Model (RFM)** for tabular and relational data, developed and maintained by SAP.\n",
    "\n",
    "Unlike Large Language Models (LLMs) that work with text, RPT-1 is designed to work directly with structured, tabular data — the kind found in spreadsheets, databases, and ERP systems.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Characteristics\n",
    "\n",
    "| | LLM (e.g. Claude) | SAP-RPT-1 |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| **Input** | Natural language text | Tabular rows (structured data) |\n",
    "| **Output** | Text response | Predicted column values + confidence scores |\n",
    "| **Use case** | Q&A, summarization, generation | Classification, regression on tabular data |\n",
    "| **Training needed** | No (zero-shot) | No (zero-shot) |\n",
    "| **Context** | Prompt text | Surrounding rows provide in-context learning |\n",
    "| **SDK support** | `init_llm` | `RPTClient` (native SDK) |\n",
    "\n",
    "### How RPT-1 Works\n",
    "\n",
    "RPT-1 uses **in-context learning** on tabular data:\n",
    "1. You provide a table with some rows that have known values for the target column.\n",
    "2. You mark the rows you want predicted with a special placeholder: **`[PREDICT]`**.\n",
    "3. RPT-1 learns the pattern from the known rows and predicts the missing values.\n",
    "4. For each prediction, RPT-1 also returns a **confidence score** (0-1).\n",
    "\n",
    "> No model training, no fine-tuning, no embeddings — just send your table and get predictions back.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Available Models\n",
    "\n",
    "| Model | Description |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| `sap-rpt-1-large` | Higher accuracy, slower |\n",
    "| `sap-rpt-1-small` | Faster, lower resource usage |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## About the Data\n",
    "\n",
    "We use the same product catalog of IT accessory products from the RAG demo. The key attributes used for prediction:\n",
    "\n",
    "|Field|Description|\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "|**PRODUCT_ID**|Unique identifier for each product|\n",
    "|**PRODUCT_NAME**|Product name including brand and model|\n",
    "|**CATEGORY**|Product category (IT Accessories)|\n",
    "|**UNIT_PRICE**|Price in Euros|\n",
    "|**MANUFACTURER**|Manufacturer name|\n",
    "|**SUPPLIER_CITY**|City where the supplier is located|\n",
    "|**STOCK_QUANTITY**|Current stock quantity|\n",
    "|**LEAD_TIME_DAYS**|Days from order to delivery|\n",
    "|**MIN_ORDER**|Minimum order quantity|\n",
    "|**RATING**|Product rating on a scale from 1 to 5 — **this is our prediction target**|\n",
    "\n",
    "</br>\n",
    "\n",
    "We will take a sample of products, hide the `RATING` for some of them with `[PREDICT]`, and ask RPT-1 to predict the rating based on the other attributes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Setup and Configuration\n",
    "\n",
    "The following Python modules are used in this notebook.\n",
    "\n",
    "#### **sap-ai-sdk-gen**\n",
    "Provides the `RPTClient` for calling SAP-RPT-1 models natively, as well as `AICoreV2Client` and `GenAIHubProxyClient` for authentication.\n",
    "\n",
    "For more information, please see https://pypi.org/project/sap-ai-sdk-gen/\n",
    "\n",
    "#### **pandas**\n",
    "Used to load and display the product catalog in tabular format.\n",
    "\n",
    "For more information, please see https://pypi.org/project/pandas/\n",
    "\n",
    "</br>\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Install Python packages"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%pip install \"sap-ai-sdk-gen[all]\" --break-system-packages -U\n",
    "%pip install requests pandas --break-system-packages -U\n",
    "\n",
    "# kernel restart required!!!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Restart Python kernel\n",
    "\n",
    "The Python kernel needs to be restarted before continuing.\n",
    "\n",
    "> ![title](./images/config_001.png)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Configure SAP AI Core credentials\n",
    "\n",
    "We load the AI Core credentials from `env_config.json` — the same file used in the RAG notebook.\n",
    "\n",
    "> Please ensure that the Python kernel was restarted!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import json\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "with open(os.path.join(os.getcwd(), 'env_config.json')) as f:\n",
    "    aicore_config = json.load(f)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\✅ Configuration loaded successfully!\")\n",
    "print(f\"   AI Core base URL : {aicore_config['AICORE_BASE_URL']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Resource group   : {aicore_config['AICORE_RESOURCE_GROUP']}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Initialize the AI Core Client\n",
    "\n",
    "We set up the `AICoreV2Client` and `GenAIHubProxyClient` using the same pattern as the RAG notebook. The `RPTClient` uses this proxy client for authentication."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from ai_core_sdk.ai_core_v2_client import AICoreV2Client\n",
    "from gen_ai_hub.proxy.gen_ai_hub_proxy import GenAIHubProxyClient\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set up the AICoreV2Client\n",
    "ai_core_client = AICoreV2Client(\n",
    "    base_url=aicore_config['AICORE_BASE_URL'],\n",
    "    auth_url=aicore_config['AICORE_AUTH_URL'],\n",
    "    client_id=aicore_config['AICORE_CLIENT_ID'],\n",
    "    client_secret=aicore_config['AICORE_CLIENT_SECRET'],\n",
    "    resource_group=aicore_config['AICORE_RESOURCE_GROUP']\n",
    ")\n",
    "# Set up the GenAIHubProxyClient\n",
    "proxy_client = GenAIHubProxyClient(ai_core_client=ai_core_client)\n",
    "print(\"\✅ AI Core Client connection is established successfully!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Initialize the RPT Client\n",
    "\n",
    "The `RPTClient` is the native SDK client for SAP-RPT-1 models. It handles authentication automatically via the `GenAIHubProxyClient` set up above.\n",
    "\n",
    "Unlike LLMs which use `init_llm`, RPT-1 uses `RPTClient` because it has a completely different API format — it works with tabular rows and `[PREDICT]` placeholders rather than text prompts."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from gen_ai_hub.proxy.native.sap import RPTClient, RPTRequest, PredictionConfig, TargetColumn\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize the RPT client (uses the proxy_client set up above)\n",
    "rpt_client = RPTClient(proxy_client=proxy_client)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Model to use: sap-rpt-1-large (higher accuracy) or sap-rpt-1-small (faster)\n",
    "RPT_MODEL = \"sap-rpt-1-large\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\✅ RPT Client initialized successfully!\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Model: {RPT_MODEL}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Load the Product Catalog\n",
    "\n",
    "We load the product catalog CSV and select a representative sample of products. This sample will serve as the input table for RPT-1."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load the full product catalog\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('data/product_catalog.csv', sep=';', encoding='utf-8-sig')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Total products in catalog: {len(df)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Columns: {list(df.columns)}\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Select the columns relevant for RPT-1 prediction\n",
    "FEATURE_COLUMNS = ['PRODUCT_ID', 'PRODUCT_NAME', 'CATEGORY', 'UNIT_PRICE',\n",
    "                   'MANUFACTURER', 'SUPPLIER_CITY', 'STOCK_QUANTITY',\n",
    "                   'LEAD_TIME_DAYS', 'MIN_ORDER', 'RATING']\n",
    "\n",
    "df_sample = df[FEATURE_COLUMNS].copy().head(12).reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Sample products (first 12):\")\n",
    "df_sample"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Prepare the RPT-1 Prediction Request\n",
    "\n",
    "RPT-1 expects the data in a specific format using pydantic models:\n",
    "- **`RPTRequest`**: the top-level request object\n",
    "- **`PredictionConfig`**: specifies which column(s) to predict\n",
    "- **`TargetColumn`**: defines the target column name and task type (`regression` or `classification`)\n",
    "- **`rows`**: list of dicts — some with known values, some with `[PREDICT]` as the placeholder\n",
    "\n",
    "We will:\n",
    "- Keep the `RATING` values for the first 9 products (these act as **in-context examples** for RPT-1)\n",
    "- Replace the `RATING` with `[PREDICT]` for the last 3 products (these are the **prediction targets**)\n",
    "\n",
    "> `RATING` is a numeric value (1-5), so we use `task_type=\"regression\"`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "PREDICT_PLACEHOLDER = \"[PREDICT]\"\n",
    "TARGET_COLUMN = \"RATING\"\n",
    "INDEX_COLUMN = \"PRODUCT_ID\"\n",
    "N_KNOWN = 9  # rows used as in-context examples\n",
    "\n",
    "rows = []\n",
    "predict_ids = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, row in df_sample.iterrows():\n",
    "    record = {\n",
    "        INDEX_COLUMN: str(row[INDEX_COLUMN]),\n",
    "        \"PRODUCT_NAME\": str(row[\"PRODUCT_NAME\"]),\n",
    "        \"CATEGORY\": str(row[\"CATEGORY\"]),\n",
    "        \"UNIT_PRICE\": float(str(row[\"UNIT_PRICE\"]).replace(',', '.')),\n",
    "        \"MANUFACTURER\": str(row[\"MANUFACTURER\"]),\n",
    "        \"SUPPLIER_CITY\": str(row[\"SUPPLIER_CITY\"]),\n",
    "        \"STOCK_QUANTITY\": int(row[\"STOCK_QUANTITY\"]) if pd.notna(row[\"STOCK_QUANTITY\"]) else 0,\n",
    "        \"LEAD_TIME_DAYS\": int(row[\"LEAD_TIME_DAYS\"]) if pd.notna(row[\"LEAD_TIME_DAYS\"]) else 0,\n",
    "        \"MIN_ORDER\": int(row[\"MIN_ORDER\"]) if pd.notna(row[\"MIN_ORDER\"]) else 0,\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    if i < N_KNOWN:\n",
    "        record[TARGET_COLUMN] = float(str(row[TARGET_COLUMN]).replace(',', '.')) if pd.notna(row[TARGET_COLUMN]) else PREDICT_PLACEHOLDER\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        record[TARGET_COLUMN] = PREDICT_PLACEHOLDER\n",
    "        predict_ids.append(str(row[INDEX_COLUMN]))\n",
    "    rows.append(record)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Build the RPTRequest using pydantic models\n",
    "rpt_request = RPTRequest(\n",
    "    prediction_config=PredictionConfig(\n",
    "        target_columns=[\n",
    "            TargetColumn(name=TARGET_COLUMN, task_type=\"regression\")\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    rows=rows\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Total rows in request : {len(rows)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Known examples        : {N_KNOWN}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Rows to predict       : {len(predict_ids)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Product IDs to predict: {predict_ids}\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "pd.DataFrame(rows)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "> The rows with `[PREDICT]` in the `RATING` column are the ones RPT-1 will predict.\n",
    "> The rows with known ratings provide the in-context learning signal."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Run the RPT-1 Prediction\n",
    "\n",
    "We call `rpt_client.predict()` with the request body and model name. RPT-1 will analyze the table, learn from the known rows, and return predictions with confidence scores for the `[PREDICT]` rows."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(f\"Sending prediction request to {RPT_MODEL}...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "response = rpt_client.predict(body=rpt_request, model_name=RPT_MODEL)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\✅ Prediction successful!\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(\"Raw predictions:\")\n",
    "print(response.predictions)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Analyze the Predictions\n",
    "\n",
    "RPT-1 returns predictions where each predicted row contains the target column with a list of prediction objects:\n",
    "```json\n",
    "[\n",
    "  {\n",
    "    \"PRODUCT_ID\": \"P001\",\n",
    "    \"RATING\": [\n",
    "      { \"prediction\": 4.2, \"confidence\": 0.87 }\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    "]\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Each prediction includes:\n",
    "- **`prediction`**: the predicted value for the target column\n",
    "- **`confidence`**: a score between 0 and 1 indicating how confident RPT-1 is in the prediction"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "predictions = response.predictions\n",
    "\n",
    "pred_summary = []\n",
    "for pred in predictions:\n",
    "    # pred may be a dict or a pydantic object — handle both\n",
    "    pred_dict = pred if isinstance(pred, dict) else pred.model_dump()\n",
    "    product_id = str(pred_dict.get(INDEX_COLUMN, ''))\n",
    "    rating_preds = pred_dict.get(TARGET_COLUMN, [])\n",
    "    if rating_preds:\n",
    "        top_pred = rating_preds[0] if isinstance(rating_preds[0], dict) else rating_preds[0].model_dump()\n",
    "        pred_summary.append({\n",
    "            'PRODUCT_ID': product_id,\n",
    "            'PREDICTED_RATING': top_pred.get('prediction'),\n",
    "            'CONFIDENCE': top_pred.get('confidence'),\n",
    "        })\n",
    "\n",
    "df_predictions = pd.DataFrame(pred_summary)\n",
    "print(f\"Predictions for {len(df_predictions)} product(s):\")\n",
    "df_predictions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Merge Predictions Back into the Product Catalog\n",
    "\n",
    "We merge the RPT-1 predictions back into the original sample table to compare the predicted ratings with the actual ratings."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df_results = df_sample.copy()\n",
    "df_results['PRODUCT_ID'] = df_results['PRODUCT_ID'].astype(str)\n",
    "df_results['ACTUAL_RATING'] = df_results['RATING']\n",
    "df_results['PREDICTED_RATING'] = None\n",
    "df_results['CONFIDENCE'] = None\n",
    "\n",
    "for pred in predictions:\n",
    "    pred_dict = pred if isinstance(pred, dict) else pred.model_dump()\n",
    "    product_id = str(pred_dict.get(INDEX_COLUMN, ''))\n",
    "    rating_preds = pred_dict.get(TARGET_COLUMN, [])\n",
    "    if rating_preds:\n",
    "        top_pred = rating_preds[0] if isinstance(rating_preds[0], dict) else rating_preds[0].model_dump()\n",
    "        mask = df_results['PRODUCT_ID'] == product_id\n",
    "        df_results.loc[mask, 'PREDICTED_RATING'] = top_pred.get('prediction')\n",
    "        df_results.loc[mask, 'CONFIDENCE'] = top_pred.get('confidence')\n",
    "\n",
    "df_comparison = df_results[df_results['PRODUCT_ID'].isin(predict_ids)][\n",
    "    ['PRODUCT_ID', 'PRODUCT_NAME', 'UNIT_PRICE', 'MANUFACTURER',\n",
    "     'ACTUAL_RATING', 'PREDICTED_RATING', 'CONFIDENCE']\n",
    "].reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Comparison: Actual vs Predicted RATING\")\n",
    "df_comparison"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Full Results Table\n",
    "\n",
    "Here is the complete sample table showing all products — both the known examples used for in-context learning and the predicted rows."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df_full = df_results[['PRODUCT_ID', 'PRODUCT_NAME', 'UNIT_PRICE', 'MANUFACTURER',\n",
    "                       'SUPPLIER_CITY', 'ACTUAL_RATING', 'PREDICTED_RATING', 'CONFIDENCE']].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "df_full['SOURCE'] = df_full['PRODUCT_ID'].apply(\n",
    "    lambda pid: 'PREDICTED' if pid in predict_ids else 'known (in-context)'\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Full results table:\")\n",
    "df_full"
   ]
  },
{
    "cell_type": "markdown",
    "metadata": {},
    "source": [
      "## Predict Multiple Target Columns\n",
      "\n",
      "RPT-1 can predict **multiple columns simultaneously**. In this example, we ask it to predict both `RATING` (regression) and `SUPPLIER_CITY` (classification) for the same set of products."
    ]
  },
  {
    "cell_type": "code",
    "execution_count": null,
    "metadata": {},
    "outputs": [],
    "source": [
      "rows_multi = []\n",
      "\n",
      "for i, row in df_sample.iterrows():\n",
      "    record = {\n",
      "        INDEX_COLUMN: str(row[INDEX_COLUMN]),\n",
      "        \"PRODUCT_NAME\": str(row[\"PRODUCT_NAME\"]),\n",
      "        \"CATEGORY\": str(row[\"CATEGORY\"]),\n",
      "        \"UNIT_PRICE\": float(str(row[\"UNIT_PRICE\"]).replace(',', '.')),\n",
      "        \"MANUFACTURER\": str(row[\"MANUFACTURER\"]),\n",
      "        \"STOCK_QUANTITY\": int(row[\"STOCK_QUANTITY\"]) if pd.notna(row[\"STOCK_QUANTITY\"]) else 0,\n",
      "        \"LEAD_TIME_DAYS\": int(row[\"LEAD_TIME_DAYS\"]) if pd.notna(row[\"LEAD_TIME_DAYS\"]) else 0,\n",
      "        \"MIN_ORDER\": int(row[\"MIN_ORDER\"]) if pd.notna(row[\"MIN_ORDER\"]) else 0,\n",
      "    }\n",
      "    if i < N_KNOWN:\n",
      "        record[\"RATING\"] = float(str(row[\"RATING\"]).replace(',', '.')) if pd.notna(row[\"RATING\"]) else PREDICT_PLACEHOLDER\n",
      "        record[\"SUPPLIER_CITY\"] = str(row[\"SUPPLIER_CITY\"])\n",
      "    else:\n",
      "        record[\"RATING\"] = PREDICT_PLACEHOLDER\n",
      "        record[\"SUPPLIER_CITY\"] = PREDICT_PLACEHOLDER\n",
      "    rows_multi.append(record)\n",
      "\n",
      "rpt_request_multi = RPTRequest(\n",
      "    prediction_config=PredictionConfig(\n",
      "        target_columns=[\n",
      "            TargetColumn(name=\"RATING\", task_type=\"regression\"),\n",
      "            TargetColumn(name=\"SUPPLIER_CITY\", task_type=\"classification\"),\n",
      "        ]\n",
      "    ),\n",
      "    rows=rows_multi\n",
      ")\n",
      "\n",
      "response_multi = rpt_client.predict(body=rpt_request_multi, model_name=RPT_MODEL)\n",
      "\n",
      "print(\"\✅ Multi-target prediction successful!\")\n",
      "print()\n",
      "print(\"Raw multi-target predictions:\")\n",
      "print(response_multi.predictions)"
    ]
  },
  {
    "cell_type": "code",
    "execution_count": null,
    "metadata": {},
    "outputs": [],
    "source": [
      "# Display multi-target predictions as a table\n",
      "multi_summary = []\n",
      "for pred in response_multi.predictions:\n",
      "    pred_dict = pred if isinstance(pred, dict) else pred.model_dump()\n",
      "    row_data = {INDEX_COLUMN: str(pred_dict.get(INDEX_COLUMN, ''))}\n",
      "    for col in ['RATING', 'SUPPLIER_CITY']:\n",
      "        col_preds = pred_dict.get(col, [])\n",
      "        if col_preds:\n",
      "            top = col_preds[0] if isinstance(col_preds[0], dict) else col_preds[0].model_dump()\n",
      "            row_data[f'PREDICTED_{col}'] = top.get('prediction')\n",
      "            row_data[f'CONFIDENCE_{col}'] = top.get('confidence')\n",
      "    multi_summary.append(row_data)\n",
      "\n",
